### Bug fixes

* Enforce `run_constrained`/`constrains` entries that reference virtual packages
  (e.g. a `constrains` on `__cuda`). Virtual packages are now requested as
  (name-only) installs so the solver -- which runs with `allow_uninstall=True` --
  cannot drop them to dodge such a constraint. Previously a constraint like
  `__cuda>=13` against a host providing `__cuda==12` was silently ignored.
  (conda/conda#10803)

